---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Swadisht"
  description="Read about how Swadisht collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <div class="bg-accent/50 py-10">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-display mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl">
        Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container py-8">
    <div class="prose max-w-none">
      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect several types of information from and about users of our Platform, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Personal Information:</strong> This includes your name, email address, phone number, delivery address, and payment information.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Order Information:</strong> Information about the food items you order, your order history, and delivery preferences.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Device Information:</strong> Information about the device you use to access our Platform, including IP address, browser type, and operating system.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Location Information:</strong> With your consent, we collect precise location information to facilitate food delivery and provide location-based services.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage Information:</strong> Information about how you use our Platform, including your browsing patterns, search queries, and interactions with our features.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Processing and delivering your orders</li>
        <li>Creating and maintaining your account</li>
        <li>Providing customer support</li>
        <li>Personalizing your experience</li>
        <li>Improving our services</li>
        <li>Communicating with you about promotions, updates, and other information related to our services</li>
        <li>Preventing fraud and ensuring the security of our Platform</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How We Share Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We may share your information with:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Restaurant Partners:</strong> To fulfill your orders and provide you with their services.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Delivery Partners:</strong> To deliver your orders to your specified location.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Service Providers:</strong> Third-party vendors who provide services on our behalf, such as payment processing, data analysis, and customer support.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> When required by law, court order, or governmental authority.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Your Choices</h2>
      <p>
        You have several choices regarding your personal information:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Account Information:</strong> You can review and update your account information by logging into your account settings.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Marketing Communications:</strong> You can opt out of receiving marketing communications from us by following the unsubscribe instructions included in such communications.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Location Information:</strong> You can control location tracking through your device settings.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies:</strong> You can manage cookies through your browser settings.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our Platform is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Changes to Our Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. Your continued use of our Platform after such modifications will constitute your acknowledgment of the modified Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
      </p>
      <p>
        Email: privacy@swadisht.com<br>
        Phone: +91 9548091747<br>
        Address: Swadisht Headquarters, Sector 12, New Delhi, India
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-8">
        Last updated: September 13, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>